Module shapes contains one parent class named shape and four derived classes (Rectangle, Circle, Triangle, Trapezoid).

Class Shape:
Two attributes x and y with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y.

Class Circle:
Two attributes x and y with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y.
Calculates the area of a circle with function area, assuming that radius is x-value.

Class Rectangle:
Two attributes x and y with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y.
Calculates the area of a rectangle with function area.

Class Triangle:
Two attributes x and y with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y.
Calculates the area of a triangle with function area.


Class Trapezoid:
Three attributes x, y and z with default value 0.00.
The value of these attributes can be set using functions set_x , set_y, set_z.
Calculates the area of a trapezoid with function area.

Class ShapeCalculatorApp:
This class defines the GUI application for the Shape Calculator.

Attributes:
result_label, calculate_button, input_entry2, input_entry3, input_label3, result_value, input_label2, input_entry1, input_label1, shape_option_menu, shape_label: These attributes represent various GUI elements used in the application.
master: Represents the main tkinter window.
Methods:
__init__(self, master): Initializes the GUI application with default values and sets up the widgets.
create_widgets(self): Creates and configures all the GUI elements, such as labels, entry fields, buttons, and option menus.
update_input_fields(self, shape): Updates the input fields based on the selected shape and clears the result value.
calculate_area(self): Calculates the area of the selected shape based on the user input and displays the result. Handles exceptions for invalid input values.



